2015", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC7712.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document improves the security of the Extensible Messaging and Presence Protocol (XMPP) in two ways.  First, it specifies how to establish a strong association between a domain name and an XML stream, using the concept of prooftypes.  Second, it describes how to securely delegate a service domain name (e.g., example.com) to a target server hostname (e.g., hosting.example.net); this is especially important in multi-tenanted environments where the same target server hosts a large number of domains."];
